<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Ambassador in Cuba (
                        Norweb
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v11</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d661</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">661</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00" n="661" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.3727/11–2246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00">November 22, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>730. <gloss target="#t_CAB1">CAB</gloss> and Dept now consider it desirable to
                    explore question holding discussions on bilateral air agreement in near future.
                    Earliest possible date around first of year due to Canadian talks here. <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>s <pb facs="0774" n="756" xml:id="pg_756"/>
                    opinion on timing desired in view of <gloss target="#t_desp1">Desp</gloss> 2205
                    of September 24.<note n="80" xml:id="d661fn80">See footnote 60, <ref target="#pg_743">p. 743</ref>.</note> Howard’s travel to Washington for
                    consultation being requested prior his return Habana.<note n="81" xml:id="d661fn81">The Commercial Attaché (Howard) was on vacation in
                        Florida.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> will be advised.<note n="82" xml:id="d661fn82">The Embassy was instructed in airgram 1440, December 6,
                        1946, to ask the Cuban Government officially whether it was agreeable to the
                        opening of negotiations shortly after the first of the year
                        (711.3727/11–2746).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
